Vagrant Installation on Ubuntu.
1. Install Git
	1.1 sudo apt-get install git-core
	1.2 Check Git version: git --version

2. Install Rugby gems: 
	2.1 sudo apt-get install rubygems
	2.2 Check Ruby's version: ruby -v
	2.3 Check Ruby Gem's version: gem -v 

3. Install virtualbox:
	3.1 Get the repository key: wget -q http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/debian/oracle_vbox.asc -O- | sudo apt-key add -
	3.2 Add it to the repository: sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/debian precise contrib" >> /etc/apt/sources.list'
	3.3 Install virtualbox: sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install virtualbox-4.2
	3.4 Check if it works: type virtualbox

4. Install Vagrant
	4.1 Go to http://downloads.vagrantup.com/ and install the latest version through Ubuntu Software Center

5. Configure Vagrant (http://www.vagrantbox.es/) (http://docs-v1.vagrantup.com/v1/docs/boxes.html)
	5.1 vagrant box add Precise http://files.vagrantup.com/precise32.box
	5.2 vagrant init Precise
	5.3 vagrant up 
	5.4 Connect to it: vagrant ssh (default password = vagrant)

6. Install & Configure Chef
	6.1 Update ruby: sudo apt-get install ruby ruby-dev libopenssl-ruby rdoc ri irb build-essential wget ssl-cert curl
	6.2 Install Chef: sudo gem install chef --no-ri --no-rdoc
	6.3 Install Knife-solo: sudo gem install knife-solo
	6.4 Configure Chef: 

7. Verififaction: 
	7.1 apache: open browser and hit against localhost
	7.2 maven: $ mvn -version
		7.2.1 maven install path: ls /usr/share/maven
		7.2.2 maven config path: ls /etc/maven
	7.3 postgresql : aptitude show postgresql

